<center> <h1> Lab 3</h1></center>

<hr WIDTH="100%">

<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the <span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Create the directory <code>lab3</code> in your <code>labs</code> directory, then move to it (you can use the <code>mv</code> or <code>pushd</code> command in Unix to move to a directory).
    </li>

    <li>
	Perform LAB 4.1 - 4.4 and LAB 4.5 <i>Options</i> 2.
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/8e/Labs/LM_Chapter04.pdf">Lab 3</a>
	in the file <code>Lab3answers.txt</code>
	locating it in directory <code>lab3</code>.</li> Then submit the file to your lab3 dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, your name, <span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> login, assignment category &amp; number [e.g. Lab 3],
	and date must be included at the top of your file.
    </li>

    <li>
    Note: for each lab program, rewrite the <u>equivalence test expression</u> if the <u><i>second</i> operand</u> for a <u>equivalence operator</u>
    is a constant (literal) so that instead the <u><i>first</i> operand</u> is the constant.<br>
    (When the first operand is a literal, see what effect that has on the compilation if you remove one of the equals signs ['='].)
    </li>

    <li>
    When you are sure that each program is working correctly, use the <code>script</code> command to display first the source file, then execution, 
    of each lab assignment program.  The <code>^D</code> character will end the <code>script</code> session.<br>
    What you enter into your <code>script</code> session will look like this:
    <code>
    <pre>
	&gt;script -a Lab3typescript.txt
	&gt;cat program1.cpp
	&gt;program1
	    (your input to program 1 is here)
	&gt;cat program1.cpp
	&gt;program2
	    (your input to program 2 is here)
	    .
	     .
	      .
	&gt;^D
    </pre>
    </code>
    Submit <code>Lab3typescript.txt</code> to the D2L Dropbox.
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
<code>
